If the tank is 1 / 4 full, then it has 1 / 4 * 400 = 100 gallons of gas in it. If the car gets 20 miles per gallon, then it can travel 20 * 100 = 2000 miles on a full tank of gas. If the car can travel 2000 miles on a full tank of gas, then it can travel 2000 / 20 = 100 miles on 5 gallons of gas. The answer: 100.
